  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a pan, add cumin seeds and toast until golden brown.",
    "Add onions, garlic, tomato puree, coriander powder, turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt. Cook for about 5 minutes until the spices are fragrant and the mixture is well combined.",
    "Slice chicken into bite-sized pieces and add them to the pan with a splash of water. Cover and let it cook over medium heat for about 10-12 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "Add rice to the pan, cover with a lid, and steam for another 15 minutes. Open the lid, stir in sour mango chutney if using, and serve hot."
